04/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski is expected to visit Tirana at the weekend.
He will meet with Albanian counterpart Fatos Nano and President Alfred Moisiu.
On Tuesday (4 January), Buckovski is scheduled to hold talks with former German Finance Minister Theo Weigel, who is to head Buckovski's team of consultants on financial and economic issues.
In other news, a new poll released Monday finds the army and the police are the most trusted institutions in Macedonia.
The survey, by the Maripan Agency, found the public has least confidence in the judiciary.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 04/01/05;
MIA - 03/01/05)
